-- Ripley to Spend $350 Million on New Andean Stores, Mercurio Says
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-10-22T12:26:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-22/ripley-to-spend-350-million-on-new-andean-stores-mercurio-says.html
Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY) ,  Chile ’s third largest
department store operator, plans to spend $350 million by 2015 to
open four new stores in Chile, 15 in Peru and 15 in Colombia, El
Mercurio said in its Oct. 21 edition.  The retailer, which currently operates only in Chile and
Peru, has secured rental contracts for 10 of its planned stores in
Colombia, Ripley Corp’s chief executive officer Lazaro Calderon
told El Mercurio in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net . 